Spectrum Mobile
See how my work helped double Spectrums Mobile customers.
View Project #2
View Project #3
In 2022, I joined an Agile creative agency and served as a UX/UI Designer for Spectrum for three years. While there, I designed/built countless webpages and ads - touching nearly every page throughout the entire spectrum.com site, (including pages for internet, TV, and business) and improving the UX for millions of customers. As the first hire on my team with a background in UX not just Graphic Design I introduced my team to many UX research methods (competitor analysis, heat-mapping, e-commerce heuristics, usability testing, information architecture, and mobile-first design). During my tenure, I mastered over a dozen software programs, helped triple our account, budget, and team through two rebrands, several client leadership restructurings, and a website re-platforming all while the agency underwent two acquisitions. We consistently delivered designs that impressed the client and contributed to a steady increase in user engagement and conversions.

Prior to working on the Spectrum account, I completed a graduate program in UX and spent over two years practicing UX Research and UI Design for several clients. I worked for a few small local businesses, in addition to cofounding a disruptive B2B SaaS startup backed by angel investors. For all of these clients, my work directly contributed to sharp increases in user and employee satisfaction, as well as boosted profits. I have developed and maintained strong rapports with all of my past employers and coworkers, and my skillset has grown tremendously over the years (as has my efficiency and confidence)! I live and breathe UX/UI and I am eager to take on new challenges transforming innovative ideas into intuitive products that delight target user groups via empathy-driven research, analytics-backed insights, and seamless design implementation.
